[@by Liberta (1960). According to this author Xenasma macrosporum, described from
Panama, is characterized by the conical, thick-walled cystidia with a broad and multirooted base, which have walls with a dextrinoid reaction and are embedded in coralloid
hyphae. According to the current taxonomic interpretation of ‘corticioid’ fungi these
features clearly indicate its position in Tubulicium. An exception is Boquiren (1971),
who considers Tubulicium and Epithele as synonyms. Oberwinkler (1965) explicitly
mentioned that this species belongs to Tubulicium, but a formal combination into Tubulicium has never been published:#Misc-exposition*]
[@Tubulicium macrosporum (Liberta) G. Moreno, comb. nov.#Nomenclature*]
[@≡ Xenasma macrosporum Liberta, Mycologia 52 (6) (1962 ‘1960’) 899.#Nomenclature*]
[@≡ Epithele macrospora (Liberta) Boquiren, Mycologia 63 (5) (1971) 949.#Nomenclature*]
[@	 Original description: Fructiﬁcatio effusa, tenuíssima, in sectione 30–50 µm crassa, alutacea, cereopruinosa, sub lente hispida; hyphae haud clarae, glutinosae, sustrato parallelae, nodoso-septatae, 1.5–2
µm diam; cystidia conica, basi multi-radicosa, tunica crassa, lamellata, extus a hyphis dendriticis
circumtexta, c. 1 µm diam., lamina interiore ad basim pseudoamyloidea, 125 –164 × 9.5 – 22.5 µm;
basidia cylindracea vel subclavata, basi biradicosa, haud clara, interdum terminalia et haud radicosa
ansa sustenta, 16.5–22.5 × 5 – 9.5 µm; sterigmata 4, crassa, 9 –11 × 2 µm gerentia; basidiosporae
hyalinae, tunica tenui, leves, haud amyloideae, indutae, oblonge cylindraceae, oblonge ellipsoideae
vel late subnaviculares, 12– 19 × 4.5 –7 µm.#Description*]
[@	 Panama, Prov. Chiriqui, Valley of upper Rio Chiriqui Viejo, 1600 –1800 m, 28.VI.1935, G.W.
Martin 2097 (IA D.P. Rogers; A.E. Liberta), type.#Misc-exposition*]

[@Tubulicium macrosporum differs from T. papillatosporum by the oblong-cylindrical,
oblong-ellipsoid to broadly navicular basidiospores, 12 –19 × 4.5–7 µm, and very thin
basidiomata measuring only 3–50 µm thick.#Misc-exposition*]
